'''Gerard of Bologna''' (died 1317) was an Italian [[Carmelite]] theologian and [[scholastic philosopher]].
A convinced [[Thomist]], he took a doctorate in theology in 1295 at the [[University of Paris]]. Subsequently he was elected general of the Carmelite Order, in 1297.<ref>[http://www.helpfellowship.org/ocds%20lessons/Lesson%201.htm History of the Order<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
